$ PowerShell: if statement

The `if` statement conditionally does or does not execute sets of other statements.

Unlike → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C, the curly braces are always required (even if only *one* statement is controlled by the `if` statement).

code {
if ( cond) {
  statement
 [statement]
}
code }

code {
if ( cond) {
  statement
 [statement]
}
else {
  statement
 [statement]
}
code }

code {
if ( cond) {
  statement
 [statement]
}
elseif(cond) {
  statement
 [statement]
else {
  statement
 [statement]
}
code }

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/operator/comparison[Comparison operators]

  → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement[Others statements]
